The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Saturday, April 09, 2005 

 Handshake

 Jerusalem, April 8 (Reuters): Israeli President Moshe Katsav said he shook hands with President Bashar al-Assad of Syria, a country formally at war with the Jewish state, and the President of Iran at the funeral of Pope John Paul today.

 It was believed to be the first time an Israeli President had shaken hands with Syrian and Iranian leaders. 




